{
  "title": "Connection",
  "order": 2,
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "A Connection (pushtopics__Connection__c) defines the authentication configuration used to connect to a Salesforce org. A Connection can act as:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ul",
      "children": [
        { "type": "p", "content": "A Source for retrieving data" },
        { "type": "p", "content": "A Target for performing actions" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "content": "image/connection/connection.png",
      "alt": "Authentication Flow Diagram"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "As shown in the diagram, Data Sync Pro handles authentication through three main paths:"
    },
    {
      "type": "ul",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "<strong>Current Org:</strong> If \"Is Current Org\" is selected, DSP runs as the Currently Logged-in User, requiring no additional credentials."
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "<strong>OAuth 2.0 Flow:</strong> For remote connections, DSP utilizes a Named Credential to authenticate via an OAuth Token."
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "<strong>Username & Password Flow:</strong> DSP authenticates using a specified Username and Password via the SFDC Login API. This path automatically manages the creation of a Remote Site Setting for the authenticated Salesforce Org."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "Current Org",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "The \"Is Current Org?\" checkbox is a field on the Connection object. Once checked, DSP operates without requiring credentials."
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "It conducts queries and DML operations based on the currently logged-in user's context, indicating that the connection pertains to the current org where DSP is installed. All security settings applicable to that user are enforced during executions."
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "For a more detailed walkthrough, refer to the video below:"
        },
        {
          "type": "video",
          "src": "https://youtu.be/70GDxXd_ju8"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "Username & Password",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "DSP supports the Username & Password authentication flow."
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "This method uses:"
        },
        {
          "type": "ul",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Username"
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Password + Security Token"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "Authentication is handled securely through Salesforce’s Named Credential feature, which stores and manages the credentials safely within the platform."
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "The steps below outline the setup process."
        },
        {
          "type": "ol",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Create a Named Credential in the org where DSP is installed:",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/username-password/named-credential-new-legacy.png",
                  "alt": "Create Named Credential"
                },
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/username-password/named-credential-setup.png",
                  "alt": "Named Credential Configurations",
                  "caption":[
                    "Username: Enter the main username of the connected organization.",
                    "Enter the user's password combined with the security token. If a security token is not applicable, omit it."
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Create a DSP Connection Record in the org where DSP is installed:",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/username-password/create-connection.png",
                  "alt": "Create Connection"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Test the Connection:",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/username-password/test-connection.png",
                  "alt": "Test Connection"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "OAuth 2.0",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "DSP supports OAuth 2.0 authentication using Salesforce security features, including:"
        },
        {
          "type": "ul",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "External Client App"
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Auth. Provider"
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Named Credential"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "p",
          "content": "The steps below outline the setup process."
        },
        {
          "type": "ol",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Create a External Client App in the remote org",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-external-client-app/00.png",
                  "alt": "Create a External Client App"
                },
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-external-client-app/1.png",
                  "alt": "Create a External Client App",
                  "caption": [
                    "Replace Contact Email with your email."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-external-client-app/2.png",
                  "alt": "Create a External Client App",
                  "caption": [
                    "Use a temporary URL for the Callback URL."
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-external-client-app/3.png",
                  "alt": "Create a External Client App"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Create an Auth. Provider in the org where DSP is installed",
              "children": [
                  {
                    "type": "image",
                    "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-auth-provider/0.png",
                    "alt": "Create a External Client App"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "image",
                    "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-auth-provider/1.png",
                    "alt": "Create a External Client App",
                    "caption":[
                      "Copy and paste the Consumer Key and Consumer Scret from the remote org: Setup -> External Client App Manager -> The External App created previously -> Settings -> OAuth Settings -> Consumer Key and Secret.",
                      "Scope: Use \"refresh_token full\" or any scopes you need."
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "image",
                    "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-auth-provider/2.png",
                    "alt": "Create a External Client App",
                    "caption":[
                      "Copy the Callback URL."
                    ]
                  }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Update the Callback URL in the remote org",
              "children": [
                {
                    "type": "image",
                    "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/update-callback-url/0.png",
                    "alt": "Create a External Client App"
                    
                    
                  }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Create a Named Credential in the org where DSP is installed",
              "children": [
                {
                    "type": "image",
                    "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-named-credential/0.png",
                    "alt": "Create a External Client App"
                    
                    
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "image",
                    "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-named-credential/1.png",
                    "alt": "Create a External Client App",
                    "caption":[
                      "URL: the domain URL of the remote org. This can be found in the \"My Domain Settings\".",
                      "Scope: Use \"refresh_token full\" or any scopes you need."
                    ]
                    
                  }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Create a DSP Connection Record in the org where DSP is installed:",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/create-connection/0.png",
                  "alt": "Create Connection"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "p",
              "content": "Test the connection",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "image",
                  "content": "image/connection/OAuth-2/test-connection/0.png",
                  "alt": "Create Connection"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
